title: Table Cover, 16th–17th century
medium:
Medium: silk, linen
Technique: appliqué on gauze weave, needle lace
description: Oblong table cover of dark green silk bordered with green net in an appliqued design of foliage in reversed scrolls that terminate in lilies. Applique is natural colored linen embroidered in dark yellow silk. Edged with natural colored needle lace.
